cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with vehicle re-identification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel two-branch neural network architecture, which involves learning efficient feature embeddings, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also mentions the use of pooling and dimension-reduced convolutional layers, which could fall under the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of vehicle attribute labels to separate similar vehicle identities, which could be related to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance cameras and public security, which could be related to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category.
